      <%= image_tag 'CO.png', alt:'beeswax', style:'max-width:720px;width:100%;min-width:500px;' %>
    </div>
    
    <p>
      Coconut oil is highly lipophilic, containing medium chain fatty acids like Lauric acid and Caprylic acid with long carbon chains. This long chain enables better penetration through the top, hydrophobic, layer of the skin to provide the moisturising effect through high absorption. The acids discussed above convert themselves into great antimicrobial and anti-fungal agents like monocaprin and monolaurin when acted upon by certain enzymes. These derivatives protect our body, both internally and externally, from conditions like Athlete’s Foot, rashes, itches, ringworm, and dermatitis.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      The long chain ensures there is less likelihood for reaction with moisture or air to preserve the pure form of coconut oil. Using the purest form via centrifugation, our manufacturing process ensures we eliminate as many impurities to provide you confidence that you can experience optimum effects of coconut oil.
    </p>
  </div>
  
