    </div>
    <p>
      Beeswax has much longer carbon chains than coconut oil, which makes it the perfect complement for coconut oil in terms of its properties. The long chain works mutually with the coconut oil for optimum absorption on the skin. The occlusive properties of beeswax provide a moisturising layer on the skin to keep your skin feeling fresh.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      The structure also includes oleate ester groups and can be up to 30-32 carbon chains in length, which potentially helps provide some of the observed anti-microbial properties.
